cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI

The paper deals with image fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It specifically focuses on remote sensing and hyperspectral-multispectral image fusion, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed strategy involves an unmixing-based formulation and a parametric model, which are both techniques commonly used in machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The paper also mentions simulations and experiments with synthetic and real data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
